						Abbott Laboratories (ABT) Shares Bought by Tufton Capital Management					

						 July 1st, 2017  - 0 comments - Filed Under -
 by Micah Haroldson 


							Filed Under: Investing - SEC Filing Articles 






Tweet










Tufton Capital Management raised its stake in shares of  Abbott Laboratories (NYSE:ABT) by 0.3% during the first quarter, Holdings Channel reports. The firm owned 116,910 shares of the healthcare product maker’s stock after buying an additional 390 shares during the period. Tufton Capital Management’s holdings in Abbott Laboratories were worth $5,192,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
A number of other institutional investors have also added to or reduced their stakes in the stock. Banco Santander S.A. acquired a new position in  Abbott Laboratories during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $5,189,000.  Perceptive Advisors LLC acquired a new position in  Abbott Laboratories during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $1,921,000.  L & S Advisors Inc acquired a new position in  Abbott Laboratories during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $468,000.  Associated Banc Corp raised its position in  Abbott Laboratories by 2.2% in the fourth quarter. Associated Banc Corp now owns 207,027 shares of the healthcare product maker’s stock valued at $7,952,000 after buying an additional 4,403 shares during the period.  Finally, Marshwinds Advisory Co. raised its position in  Abbott Laboratories by 118.2% in the first quarter. Marshwinds Advisory Co. now owns 66,576 shares of the healthcare product maker’s stock valued at $2,957,000 after buying an additional 36,069 shares during the period. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  71.10% of the company’s stock. 
Shares of Abbott Laboratories (NYSE:ABT) opened at 48.61 on Friday. Abbott Laboratories has a 12-month low of $37.38 and a 12-month high of $49.59. The stock has a 50 day moving average of $46.26 and a 200-day moving average of $43.65. The company has a market capitalization of $84.35 billion, a PE ratio of 50.58 and a beta of 1.08. 




Abbott Laboratories (NYSE:ABT) last released its earnings results on Wednesday, April 19th. The healthcare product maker reported $0.48 earnings per share for the quarter, topping the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.43 by $0.05. Abbott Laboratories had a net margin of 6.74% and a return on equity of 14.91%. The firm had revenue of $6.34 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $6.16 billion. During the same period in the prior year, the firm earned $0.41 earnings per share. The business’s quarterly revenue was up 29.7% compared to the same quarter last year.  Analysts predict that  Abbott Laboratories will post $2.47 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
The company also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Tuesday, August 15th. Investors of record on Friday, July 14th will be paid a dividend of $0.265 per share. The ex-dividend date is Wednesday, July 12th. This represents a $1.06 dividend on an annualized basis and a dividend yield of 2.18%. Abbott Laboratories’s payout ratio is 110.42%. 
ILLEGAL ACTIVITY WARNING: “Abbott Laboratories (ABT) Shares Bought by Tufton Capital Management” was first  posted by Watch List News and is the property of of Watch List News. If you are viewing this piece of content on another domain, it was illegally copied and republished in violation of US & international copyright laws. The original version of this piece of content can be viewed at https://www.watchlistnews.com/abbott-laboratories-abt-shares-bought-by-tufton-capital-management/1406233.html. 
Several equities research analysts have recently weighed in on the stock. Zacks Investment Research downgraded shares of Abbott Laboratories from a “hold” rating to a “sell” rating in a research note on Tuesday, March 28th. Jefferies Group LLC  reissued a “buy” rating and issued a $52.00 target price (up previously from $51.00) on shares of Abbott Laboratories in a research note on Saturday, March 11th. BMO Capital Markets downgraded shares of Abbott Laboratories from an “outperform” rating to a “market perform” rating and set a $48.00 target price on the stock. in a research note on Tuesday, March 14th. TheStreet raised shares of Abbott Laboratories from a “c+” rating to a “b” rating in a research note on Wednesday, March 8th. Finally, Stifel Nicolaus  reissued a “buy” rating and issued a $49.00 target price on shares of Abbott Laboratories in a research note on Tuesday, April 18th. Three equities research analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating, twelve have assigned  a buy rating and one  has issued  a strong buy rating to the company’s stock. The company  has a consensus rating of “Buy” and a consensus price target of $51.57.
In related news, insider Jared Watkin sold 552 shares of the company’s stock in a transaction that occurred on Thursday, June 15th. The shares were sold at an average price of $47.97, for a total transaction of $26,479.44. Following the sale, the insider now directly owns 47,090 shares in the company, valued at $2,258,907.30. The transaction was disclosed in a legal filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which can be accessed through this link. Also, insider Stephen R. Fussell sold 196,550 shares of the company’s stock in a transaction that occurred on Thursday, June 8th. The stock was sold at an average price of $46.00, for a total transaction of $9,041,300.00. Following the sale, the insider now owns 221,488 shares in the company, valued at $10,188,448. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Insiders have sold 206,902 shares of company stock worth $9,497,761 over the last 90 days. Insiders own  0.76% of the company’s stock. 
About Abbott Laboratories
Abbott Laboratories is engaged in the discovery, development, manufacture and sale of a range of healthcare products. The Company operates through four segments: Established Pharmaceutical Products, Diagnostic Products, Nutritional Products and Vascular Products. Its Established Pharmaceutical Products include a range of branded generic pharmaceuticals manufactured around the world and marketed and sold outside the United States.
